South Valley Cement Board Approves Plan to Buy Back of 3 Million Shares

-- B y   A l a a   S h a h i n e
-- 
2011-05-02T09:56:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-02/south-valley-cement-board-approves-plan-to-buy-back-of-3-million-shares.html
South Valley Cement (SVCE) , an Egyptian
cement maker, said its board of directors approved a plan to buy
back 3 million shares.  The buyback program is aimed at “supporting the shares in
the market” and is a “good investment opportunity for the
company,” Cairo-based South Valley said in a regulatory filing
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alaa Shahine in Cairo at 
 asalha@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
